NemotronH MTP + radix cache (PR #27998) patch-application step for
container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly.

Adds one COPY+RUN step that applies sglang-nemotronh-mtp-pr27998.patch
(upstream PR #27998 — enable native MTP / speculative decoding together
with radix prefix cache for NemotronH) to the sglang Python source AFTER
the SM121 sgl-kernel patches but BEFORE `uv pip install ./python`, so the
installed package picks up the changes. Same pattern as
dockerfile-dsv4-nvfp4.patch.

Apply to: container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly AFTER
dockerfile-sm121.patch has been applied. Application is gated by
build_sm121_image.sh on the recipe variable APPLY_NEMOTRONH_MTP_PR27998=1
(set in sglang-0.5.13-dev-nemotronh-mtp-sm121.recipe; remove the variable /
set 0 once PR #27998 is merged into the pinned SGLANG_REF).

NOTE: anchors on the SAME Dockerfile region as dockerfile-dsv4-nvfp4.patch
and dockerfile-gemma4-nvfp4.patch (the end of the sm121-debug block). These
are mutually exclusive per recipe (no nemotronh+dsv4+gemma4 recipe exists);
the dry-run below catches it if that ever changes.

--- a/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
+++ b/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
@@ -290,6 +290,22 @@
         echo "=== Skipping sgl-kernel-sm121-debug.patch (APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG=${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG}) ==="; \
     fi

+# NemotronH MTP + radix cache (upstream PR #27998, not yet merged).
+# Captured against main merge-base 2a51479a; applied onto v0.5.13 (see the
+# source patch header). Enables native MTP (speculative decoding) together
+# with radix (prefix) cache so no --disable-radix-cache is needed. Applied to
+# the sglang Python source before pip install so the installed dist-packages
+# picks up the changes. This COPY+RUN step only exists in builds whose recipe
+# sets APPLY_NEMOTRONH_MTP_PR27998=1 (the dockerfile patch adding this step is
+# gated by build_sm121_image.sh).
+COPY patches/sglang-nemotronh-mtp-pr27998.patch /tmp/sglang-nemotronh-mtp-pr27998.patch
+RUN set -e; cd /data/sglang && \
+    echo "=== Applying sglang-nemotronh-mtp-pr27998.patch (PR #27998) ===" && \
+    patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sglang-nemotronh-mtp-pr27998.patch && \
+    patch -p1 < /tmp/sglang-nemotronh-mtp-pr27998.patch && \
+    grep -q 'speculative decoding (MTP) together with radix' python/sglang/srt/arg_groups/nemotron_h_hook.py && \
+    echo 'NemotronH MTP PR #27998 patch applied successfully'
+
 # Install sglang package (no deps, no build isolation since base has torch).
 # Moved here from its original early-stage location so the installed
 # dist-packages picks up the patched nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh above.
